The paper describes the functionalities of the SBS Brand Intelligence App, which analyzes big textual data to assess brand importance and provide brand analytics. This involves combining methods and tools from social network analysis and text mining. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the organization and retrieval of information from large datasets. 

The paper also involves analyzing networks of co-occurring words, which suggests the sub-categories cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses monitoring consumer perceptions and associations of the brand, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) or cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy).
